## 1. 🔍 Threat Model — OWASP Top 10

| # | Threat | Risk Level | Mitigation |
|---|--------|------------|------------|
| 1 | SQL Injection | HIGH | JPA/Hibernate parameterized queries. No raw SQL in codebase. |
| 2 | JWT Token Theft | HIGH | Stateless JWT with expiry. HTTPS in production. Short TTL. |
| 3 | Broken Authentication | HIGH | BCrypt password hashing via `BCryptPasswordEncoder`. |
| 4 | Broken Access Control | HIGH | Spring Security `JwtAuthFilter` on all `/api/**`. RBAC with ADMIN/MANAGER/VIEWER roles using `@PreAuthorize`. |
| 5 | Prompt Injection (AI) | MEDIUM | Input sanitisation middleware in Flask — strips HTML, detects injection patterns, returns 400. |
| 6 | Rate Limit Bypass | MEDIUM | `flask-limiter` at 30 req/min on all AI endpoints, 10 req/min on `/generate-report`. Returns 429 with `retry_after`. |
| 7 | Sensitive Data / PII Exposure | HIGH | No PII in `audit_plan` table. No personal data in Groq prompts. Error messages return generic JSON only. |
| 8 | XSS Attack | MEDIUM | React escapes all output by default. No `dangerouslySetInnerHTML`. Security headers added. |
| 9 | Hardcoded Secrets | HIGH | All secrets use `${ENV_VAR}` in `application.yml`. `.env` is in `.gitignore`. GROQ_API_KEY never in source code. |
| 10 | IDOR (Insecure Direct Object Reference) | MEDIUM | Role + ownership checks in service layer. Soft delete used. All endpoints require valid JWT. |

